{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fb39660f-b0cd-423d-b417-2f7d8ba72861","content":"I can help you analyze your .NET crash dump. Here's how to proceed:\n\n**Tools for analysis:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, recommended):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-dump analyze <path-to-your.dmp>\n   ```\n   Useful commands inside the analyzer:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n   - `pe` — print the last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n   - `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n2. **WinDbg** (Windows, with SOS extension) or **lldb** (Linux, with SOS plugin)\n\n**Would you like me to:**\n- Run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your dump file here? If so, provide the file path.\n- Walk you through specific commands to investigate a particular symptom (hang, OOM, access violation, unhandled exception)?\n\nLet me know the path to your `.dmp` file and any details about the crash (e.g., error message, exception type) and I'll dig in.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"519fbe1f-4c75-4ed6-97e9-6c2f240b157a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants help analyzing it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me help them with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It specifically says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill isn't appropriate here. Let me provide guidance on analyzing the dump file directly.\n\nI should help them analyze the dump using tools like `dotnet-dump analyze` or similar. Let me ask where the dump file is located and provide guidance.","outputTokens":451,"requestId":"C3C7:1ED388:1D60541:20F9BB8:6A07C3AD"},"id":"cb1e25cf-4e80-4730-8f3c-b6ae68687588","timestamp":"2026-05-16T